trend_summary: Built-up surfaces grow steadily from scattered settlements to a modest town core with satellite housing, while most of the territory remains cropland and woodland. New industrial clusters appear beside the main highway and a bypass ring. Some marginal fields revert to forest, so impervious cover rises moderately but landscape still reads mainly rural.
notable_changes: Town centre footprint expands and coalesces with nearby villages, roughly doubling residential area.
Industrial/warehouse complex emerges on eastern edge beside primary road after mid-series.
New bypass or ring-road constructed, increasing road density around central settlement.
Several former cropland patches in the south and west show progressive reforestation or pasture abandonment.
Small housing estates infill along the north-west corridor, converting field blocks into low-density suburbia.
